<task id="AIPU2-117" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>SprkChat regression test for all 23 SSE event types</title>
    <phase>6</phase>
    <tags>testing, regression, sprkchat</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-079, AIPU2-062</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    SprkChat's SSE event handling is the core streaming UX for the entire platform. The R2
    ConversationPane integration (AIPU2-079) and the expanded SSE event set (AIPU2-062) must
    not have broken any of the original event types. This regression test verifies all 23 SSE
    event types function correctly end-to-end in the R2 ConversationPane context. Each event
    type must produce the correct UI change, including the new R2 types added during this
    project. This is a blocking gate before deployment.
  </prompt>
  <role>Frontend developer with deep knowledge of the SprkChat SSE streaming protocol.</role>
  <goal>
    All 23 SSE event types produce the correct UI behavior in the R2 ConversationPane.
    A test matrix documents each event type, the trigger condition, the expected UI change,
    and the actual result. Zero regressions from R1 behavior. All new R2 event types work
    as designed.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r2/design.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/SprkChat</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/ConversationPane</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Streaming</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Document the complete SSE event type list (23 events): token, done, error, suggestions, citations, typing_start, typing_end, plan_preview, plan_step_start, plan_step_complete, document_processing_start, document_processing_complete, document_processing_error, action_confirmation, action_success, action_error, dialog_open, navigate, document_stream_start, document_stream_token, document_stream_end, plus any new R2 event types from AIPU2-062. Confirm the count is 23.</step>
    <step>For each event type, define: trigger condition (how to produce this event from the backend), expected SprkChat UI change, expected ConversationPane state change.</step>
    <step>Write a mock SSE server or use existing test infrastructure to produce controlled SSE streams with specific event sequences.</step>
    <step>Test original R1 event types (token, done, error, suggestions, citations, typing_start/end): verify each produces correct UI in the R2 ConversationPane context. These must be identical to R1 behavior.</step>
    <step>Test plan events (plan_preview, plan_step_start, plan_step_complete): verify plan steps render correctly in the ConversationPane message thread and that step completion animates correctly.</step>
    <step>Test document processing events: verify document_processing_start shows a progress indicator, complete hides it, error shows an inline error message.</step>
    <step>Test action events (action_confirmation, action_success, action_error): verify confirmation prompt appears with approve/reject affordance, success dismisses it, error shows inline error.</step>
    <step>Test navigation and dialog events (dialog_open, navigate): verify dialog_open triggers the correct dialog widget, navigate triggers workspace tab navigation.</step>
    <step>Test document stream events (document_stream_start/token/end): verify the document streams into a workspace tab correctly with progressive rendering.</step>
    <step>Test new R2 event types from AIPU2-062: verify each new event type produces the expected R2-specific UI behavior.</step>
    <step>Document all 23 results in notes/sprkchat-regression-test-report.md with pass/fail per event type.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>All 23 SSE event types are documented with trigger condition and expected UI behavior.</criterion>
    <criterion>All original R1 event types (token, done, error, etc.) produce identical behavior in the R2 ConversationPane.</criterion>
    <criterion>All plan events render step-by-step progress correctly.</criterion>
    <criterion>All document processing events show correct progress/error states.</criterion>
    <criterion>All action events show confirmation prompts and handle approve/reject correctly.</criterion>
    <criterion>All document stream events produce correct progressive rendering in workspace.</criterion>
    <criterion>All new R2 event types work as designed.</criterion>
    <criterion>Zero regressions — all 23 event types pass.</criterion>
    <criterion>Test report written to notes/sprkchat-regression-test-report.md with per-event-type pass/fail matrix.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
